    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-02-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="80"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 324.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">London,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-02-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 13, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received from Mr. Sprague, the consul at
                    Gibraltar, a telegram announcing that the Sumter left the port of Gibraltar on
                    the night of the 7th instant, in a very high wind, when it was impossible to
                    communicate with the Chippeway. He reports her as bound westward.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
